  "description": [
    "THE WASHINGTON DAILY NEWS WEDNESDAY DECEMBER 16 1942 OPA Statement Fails to Please Dealers Government and Scott Meet to Halt Oil Woe OPA and ODT officials today met with Lester Scott head of the oilheating division of the I Merchants Manufacturers Association to take up with him his complaint that retail fueloil deliveries have broken down locally due to rationing regulations and that no one in the Govern ment apparently was interested in doing anything about it This followed announcement by price Administrator Leon Henderson ad ODT Director Joseph B East man that the ration program as op l erated promised sufficiently frequent I retail deliveries of oil this winter to provide home owners with their I share of the limited supply only to I run into an immediate denunciation from the campaigning leader of Wash I ingtons retailers MISLEADING he says That statement is misleading the public Mr Scott declared There is nothing new in it It seeks to point out that everything is going to b all right simply by going on the way we are under the rationing pro gram It comes at a time when matters are only getting worse here My checkup this morning showed"
  ],
